Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C) In a bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In a large bowl, whisk together sugar, butter, eggs, lemon zest and lemon extract. Using a wooden spoon, stir in flour mixture alternating with milk, making three additions of flour and two of milk, just until blended. Scoop batter evenly into prepared tin. Bake in preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, 18 to 22 minutes. Let cool in tin on a wire rack for 10 minutes before transferring to rack to cool completely. Decorate cooled cupcakes with any of the icings(see Notes).